emotes.msg: My stars! I can work the carapace of such a creature, but working this is beyond me. You say you found this on Marae? Well, maybe someone there could help you with this. I hear that one of the Tumerok tribes killed a queen.
Thank you so much for showing me this - I've never seen the like!
I collect olthoi trophies.  If you're willing to give yours up, I'll return part of it as a useful item.
Well, you'll look rather like a bug in this.
Just when I thought I knew all the derivations of these creatures, you bring me this!
You have a good head on your shoulders, keep it there. Perhaps this will help do so.
Thank you. Accept these tassets, please.
May these serve you well.
Ah! Best hope she does not seek you out to get this back!
If she succeeds while you are wearing this, you can then return the favor.
May these serve you well.
This could be useful.
Here, something for your feet. Some sensible sollerets.
Such a monster... such a horror.
The thorax makes a fine girth, however!

You're lucky you survived. All we can deduce about the smallest of the olthoi assault troops is that they serve the purpose of entering small places. They also are the fastest and strongest of their species. Wear this helmet with pride, you have earned the respect of many with this kill.
Here are some pauldrons made from the foul creature.

Asheron said that I should be expecting these sometime soon. He also gave me a nice selection of rewards for the efforts of those that helped out. Give me a just a moment while I sort through the items.
